Input function constructor for list input

Input function constructor for list input

This is particularly useful when constructing dynamic length of inputs for models like recurrent neural networks.

# S3 method for list
input_fn(x, features, response)

Arguments

x

The list that represents the input source
features

The names of features to be used
response

The response variable name to be used

See also

Other input function constructors: input_function_rectangular

Examples

input_fn1 <- input_fn(
   x = list(
     feature_names = list(
       list(list(1), list(2), list(3)),
       list(list(4), list(5), list(6))),
     response = list(
       list(1, 2, 3), list(4, 5, 6))),
   features = c("feature_names"),
   response = "response")
